Reasoning: The paper discusses algorithm design paradigms and their applicability to linguistic structure, which suggests a focus on natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the limits of algorithmic approaches, which suggests a focus on machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses recursion and breaking down problems into sub-problems, which suggests a focus on algorithms and data structures (DS), making cs.SD (Systems and Control) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) possible sub-categories.
